<div class="header">
  <h1>🏠 OzNet Infrastructure Hub</h1>
  <p>Simplified infrastructure with Cloudflare Tunnel</p>
</div>

<section class="card">
  <h2>📋 What is OzNet?</h2>
  <p>
    OzNet is a <strong>minimal infrastructure repository</strong> that provides:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cloudflare Tunnel</strong> for secure public access to services</li>
    <li><strong>This Hub</strong> for monitoring and documentation</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <em>All business services live in separate, independent repositories.</em>
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>🏗️ Architecture</h2>
  
  <h3>Public Access Model</h3>
  <p>All public services use Cloudflare Tunnel:</p>
  <pre>Internet → Cloudflare (TLS) → Tunnel → localhost:PORT → Service</pre>
  
  <ul>
    <li>✅ Cloudflare handles all TLS/SSL termination</li>
    <li>✅ No ports exposed directly to internet</li>
    <li>✅ DDoS protection and WAF included</li>
    <li>✅ Each service listens on localhost only</li>
    <li>✅ Each service has its own subdomain</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>📊 Service Status</h2>
  <p>Current status of services defined in <code>infrastructure/cloudflare/tunnel-config.yml</code>:</p>
  
  {{#if services}}
    <div class="service-grid">
      {{#each services}}
        <div class="card">
          <h3>
            <a href="https://{{name}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{{name}}</a>
          </h3>
          <p><small><code>{{url}}</code></small></p>
          <p>
            <strong>Status:</strong> 
            <span class="status-badge {{#if (eq status 'UP')}}status-up{{else}}status-down{{/if}}">
              {{status}}
            </span>
          </p>
        </div>
      {{/each}}
    </div>
  {{else}}
    <p><em>No services found in tunnel config.</em></p>
  {{/if}}
</section>

<section class="architecture-section card">
  <h2>🎯 Service Organization</h2>
  
  <h3>How Services Work</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Each service is independent</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Lives in its own repository</li>
        <li>Has its own deployment pipeline</li>
        <li>Runs on a unique localhost port</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Services implement /health endpoint</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Returns HTTP 200 when healthy</li>
        <li>This hub monitors all services</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Public access via Cloudflare Tunnel</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Configure in <code>infrastructure/cloudflare/tunnel-config.yml</code></li>
        <li>Each service gets its own subdomain</li>
        <li>Cloudflare handles SSL automatically</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>

